 Using a necro to PL my monk</span><hr size=1> Kaesora?  I'm not sure your pet will fair well without help, anywhere. <p>~Morb <BR> [60 Grandmaster] <A HREF=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83772 >Heeman</A> (human) <Exiled Alliance><BR><BR><BR><CENTER><I><font size=1>Courage is grace under pressure-Ernest Hemingway</font></I></CENTER><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tarrask>Tarrask</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/30/02 9:51:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1914.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Using a necro to PL my monk</span><hr size=1> Interesting idea - it could work - but to my mind a better plan would be not to group the pair, use a low level darkness and fear from the necro, and set the monk on the mob as your pet.  The monk would then get 100% xp.  DL would be a good location, just turn off OOC =)<br><br>If you wanted to go with the original plan I'd suggest one of the Kunark dungeons too.  Kaesora, maybe Droga. <p>Tarrask, 52nd Swifttail of Saryrn<BR><BR>Do not walk before me, for I may not follow.  Do not walk behind me, for I may not lead.  Do not walk beside me either, just leave me the hell alone. <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231234/" target="_blank"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukrankenthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kranken the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/30/02 10:14:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1914.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://saedyan.freesehttp://pages.prodigy.net/cohmsford/america.gifrvers.com/images/pstgif.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Using a necro to PL my monk</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The plan was to group him with my monk, feign the monk and then go afk for a couple hours while the necro pet kills the mobs.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Pets can no longer be aggroed by mobs... unless you have the necro standing near the pet and tanking the mobs while it kils them this probably wouldn't work. <p> <br><a href="http://spacefem.com/uselessquiz/index.shtml"> <img src="http://spacefem.com/uselessquiz/7.gif" border=0> </a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uugle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ugle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/7/02 2:36:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1914.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ugleduklin.tripod.com/sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/dscn0011s.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Using a necro to PL my monk</span><hr size=1> Just have them group.  I have a Monk/BL combo (L54/55), but I'm swapping the BL out for a Shaman.  Once the Shaman hit 37 I had the BL and Shammie group (Shaman will be switching accounts, but is grouping with the BL ATM).  Last night I entered Kaesora 1 kill into L40, and around 3 hours later left with the Shammy at 41.  EXP is actually faster grouped then it was solo, unless you have a Druid or such to PL.  <br><br>In the time you are standing there watching the Monk get the MOB to 49% health, your pet and the Monk could have easily killed 3, maybe 5 more MOB's.  Around 3 passes through Kaesora and he should be L41.  CoM was also decent.  And Rockhopper in DSP were excellent.  Pretty nice when you have a MOB the higher levels pet can solo and yet you get 2/3 or a blue or so per kill...<br><br>Ideally you want stuff that is lt. blue to green to the higher level so that he can mow through them, evens or above to the lower level.  Without using &quot;standard&quot; PL techniques (DS+regen+heals), I've been making 1.5-2 levels a night from 37 on, and expect to get from just 41 to Planar by next weekend.  Now that I'm 41 I'll probably head to Guk, making a level a night there till 48 or higher should not be all that bad.... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urabbokarabekian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rabbo karabekian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/8/02 9:24:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1914.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> kaesora</span><hr size=1> Kaesora is the way to go.  Just bring them both down the xalgoz area, raise a pet and start killing away.  you could even feign the monk but easier if they are both killing.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=1914.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showNextMessage?topicID=1914.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWe